The Federal High court in Abuja has approved that the Department of State Services (DSS) detain Omoyele Sowore for 45 days. Sowore, who is the publisher of online news medium, Sahara Reporters, was picked up in the wee hours of Saturday by Department of State Services (DSS) operatives from his house in Lagos. The DSS later explained their action on the ground that they could not allow anyway threaten the peace and security of the nation. The police also said Soworeâ€™s action was reasonable felony. 